---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/flowbite@3.1.2/dist/flowbite.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />

<MainLayout
  title="Ecommerce Agency | Digital Marketing Company "
  description="Laravel ecommerce agency who can help your business grow. Discover our laravel ecommerce package and learn what you can use today."
>
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="py-8 px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl text-center lg:py-16 lg:px-12">
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-none text-gray-900 md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl dark:text-white">
        Ecommerce Agency London
      </h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-lg font-normal text-gray-500 lg:text-xl sm:px-16 xl:px-48 dark:text-gray-400">
        Usually the developers are building <a href="#" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">e-commerce platforms with Laravel</a> and the question of the best CMS or package is common. 
        Our laravel company has comperd all the <a href="https://laravelcompany.com">laravel e-commerce packages</a> Aimeos, Bagisto, Lunar, and Vanilo, to identify the top performers and how they differ from our Laravel Ecommerce Package.
        While the general e-commerce market features well-known names like Magento, PrestaShop, WooCommerce, and Shopify, developers specifically looking for Laravel-integrated solutions also have a solid range of options. This is an honest review from a marketing manager with a strong background in e-commerce, including the launch of the <b>Samsung Galaxy S9</b>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 py-12">
    <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl lg:px-6">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-sm text-center mb-8 lg:mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl lg:text-4xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Aimeos: Features & Capabilities
        </h2>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-500 sm:text-xl dark:text-gray-400">
          Build full-featured, ultra-fast online shops, marketplaces, or complex B2B applications. Aimeos is cloud-native, API-first, and scales from 1 to 1,000,000,000+ items.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Multi-Vendor & Multi-Channel</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Capable of handling multi-vendor, multi-channel, and multi-warehouse setups. Build marketplaces, B2B apps, and reseller systems with tree-like multi-tenancy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Versatile Product Types</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Supports bundles, events, vouchers, virtual, configurable, custom, and group products, including paid downloads and custom attributes.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">High Scalability (#gigacommerce)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            For shops from one to 1,000,000,000+ items that render in 20ms. Uses ElasticSearch to scale infinitely.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Subscription Ready</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Turn any product into a subscription with recurring payments, automatically captured from the payment provider.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">100+ Payment Gateways</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Integrates with Omnipay PHP library for major payment providers like PayPal, Stripe, and many more.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Multi-Tenant SaaS</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Host unlimited shops in one installation for merchants, each with its own products, inventories, and order management.
          </p>
        </div>
         <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">JSON REST & GraphQL API</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Build custom frontends, PWAs, and native mobile apps using the JSON REST API. Manage shop content with the GraphQL admin API.
          </p>
        </div>
         <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Google Lighthouse Optimized</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
            Achieves top scores in performance, accessibility, best practices, and SEO.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16">
        <h3 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-semibold text-center text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Laravel eCommerce Showcases
        </h3>
        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
            Aimeos is used world-wide by thousands of companies. Below is a small selection. Discover more: <a href="#" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">Aimeos Showcases</a>.
        </p>
        <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md dark:bg-gray-700 dark:border-gray-600">
            <h4 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Showcase Example 1</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Brief description of the showcase.</p>
            <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center mt-4 font-medium text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-500 dark:hover:text-blue-700">
                View Project
                <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10.293 3.293a1 1 0 011.414 0l6 6a1 1 0 010 1.414l-6 6a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L14.586 11H3a1 1 0 110-2h11.586l-4.293-4.293a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
          </div>
        <div class="text-center mt-8">
            <a href="#" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">
                Take a look at the Aimeos demo setups (Aimeos Laravel ecommerce demo)
            </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16">
        <h3 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-semibold text-center text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          The Simplest Way to Laravel Ecommerce
        </h3>
        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
            Get your own shop in less than 5 minutes by simply executing the following command.
        </p>
        <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
          <figure class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
            <figcaption class="text-sm text-center text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">Aimeos Headless</figcaption>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <pre><code class="language-bash">composer create-project aimeos/aimeos-headless myshop</code></pre>
            </div>
          </figure>
          <figure class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
            <figcaption class="text-sm text-center text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">Aimeos Standalone Shop</figcaption>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <pre><code class="language-bash">composer create-project aimeos/aimeos myshop</code></pre>
            </div>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center mt-8">
            <a href="#" class="py-2.5 px-5 me-2 mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 focus:outline-none bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-100 hover:text-blue-700 focus:z-10 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-100 dark:focus:ring-gray-700 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400 dark:border-gray-600 dark:hover:text-white dark:hover:bg-gray-700">
                Get Aimeos
            </a>
        </div>
      </div>

       <div class="mt-16">
        <h3 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-semibold text-center text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Build Your Custom Laravel Ecommerce Easily
        </h3>
        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
            You can fully customize your Laravel ecommerce project. There are Laravel facades for all relevant areas:
        </p>
        <figure class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white p-4 rounded-lg">
<pre><code class="language-php">
use \Aimeos\Shop\Facades\Product;

$items = Product::uses(['text', 'media', 'price'])
    ->category(123)->text('sneaker')
    ->sort('name')->slice(0, 48)->search();
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16" id="accordion-collapse" data-accordion="collapse">
        <h3 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-semibold text-center text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Aimeos Laravel eCommerce FAQ
        </h3>
        <div>
          <h2 id="accordion-collapse-heading-1">
            <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border border-b-0 border-gray-200 rounded-t-xl focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-200 dark:focus:ring-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-collapse-body-1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="accordion-collapse-body-1">
              <span>Is Aimeos an application or a library?</span>
              <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
                <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
              </svg>
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="accordion-collapse-body-1" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-collapse-heading-1">
            <div class="p-5 border border-b-0 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 dark:bg-gray-900">
              <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">It's available as both, an easy to install Laravel shop distribution, a Laravel headless distribution and a Laravel ecommerce package. The first ones are very easy to install while you can integrate the package into your own, already existing Laravel application.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">The Aimeos shop distribution and Aimeos headless distribution are preconfigured setup based on the latest Laravel LTS release. They are an out of the box solution which are also prepared for multi-vendor setups. Contrary to the distribution, the Aimeos Laravel ecommerce package can be integrated into any existing Laravel application instead.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h2 id="accordion-collapse-heading-2">
            <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border border-b-0 border-gray-200 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-200 dark:focus:ring-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-collapse-body-2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-collapse-body-2">
              <span>Is Aimeos Open Source?</span>
              <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
                <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
              </svg>
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="accordion-collapse-body-2" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-collapse-heading-2">
            <div class="p-5 border border-b-0 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
              <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Yes, the Aimeos Laravel eCommerce platform is Open Source and available under the LGPLv3 licence. The Laravel integration itself is licensed using the MIT license. Both allow you to modify and/or redistribute the Aimeos source code. You can use it in any of your client projects for free and without restrictions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
           <h2 id="accordion-collapse-heading-3">
            <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border border-gray-200 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-200 dark:focus:ring-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-collapse-body-3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-collapse-body-3">
              <span>How much does Aimeos cost?</span>
              <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
                <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
              </svg>
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="accordion-collapse-body-3" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-collapse-heading-3">
            <div class="p-5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
              <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Nothing! It's free of charge and, most importantly, you can use it for all your Laravel ecommerce projects without paying anything.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">There are only a few extensions for B2B, marketplaces and #gigacommerce offered by the Aimeos company which are not available for free. In addition, the Aimeos company offers paid support if you need 1:1 developer support. They also offer support for all Aimeos LTS version up to five years.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          {/* Repeat for all FAQ questions and answers, adjusting IDs and controls */}
            <h2 id="accordion-collapse-heading-aimeos-vs-magento">
                <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border border-gray-200 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-200 dark:focus:ring-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 gap-3" data-accordion-target="#accordion-collapse-body-aimeos-vs-magento" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-collapse-body-aimeos-vs-magento">
                <span>What are the benefits of Aimeos over Magento?</span>
                <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
                    <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
                </svg>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="accordion-collapse-body-aimeos-vs-magento" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-collapse-heading-aimeos-vs-magento">
                <div class="p-5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Aimeos is much more lightweight. The Aimeos Laravel ecommerce platform only contains around 1/5th of the code of the Magento core for roughly the same feature set. In additon, the optimized data structures makes Aimeos extremely fast. You can achieve a render time down to 20ms for cached components without the problems of a full page cache as used by Magento.</p>
                <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">It also scales much better than Magento. Magento works fine up to 50k products but will get slower and slower with more products. Contrary to Magento, Aimeos can utilize ElasticSearch of Solr as drop-in replacement for storing and/or searching/filtering products. Thus, building Laravel shops with 1,000,000,000+ products is possible without any performance loss by using the Aimeos #gigacommerce extension.</p>
                <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Moreover, Laravel is currently the best PHP framwork. It's much easier to use than the old Zend framework Magento is based on and developers are more productive when using Laravel. There's also a lot of documentation and videos available for Laravel and it has a very big developer community.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            {/* Add more FAQ items similarly for all questions */}
            {/* Example for the last FAQ item for brevity */}
            <h2 id="accordion-collapse-heading-vuejs">
                <button type="button" class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-5 font-medium rtl:text-right text-gray-500 border border-gray-200 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-200 dark:focus:ring-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 gap-3 rounded-b-xl" data-accordion-target="#accordion-collapse-body-vuejs" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-collapse-body-vuejs">
                <span>Is Aimeos using Vue.js? (Example of a rephrased duplicate from your original: "Is the Aimeos frontend SEO optimized?")</span>
                <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-3 h-3 rotate-180 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 10 6">
                    <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"/>
                </svg>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="accordion-collapse-body-vuejs" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-collapse-heading-vuejs">
                <div class="p-5 border border-t-0 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Yes, Aimeos uses Vue.js in the admin backend. It offers Vue.js components for a large number of building blocks which can be reused in custom panels easily.</p>
                <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">If you want to create a frontend based on Vue.js, Aimeos offers a world class JSON REST API for retrieving and managing data. The API allows to you build a Vue.js frontend with the same feature set as the HTML based frontend.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl lg:px-6">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-sm text-center mb-8 lg:mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl lg:text-4xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Bagisto: Alternatives and Features
        </h2>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-500 sm:text-xl dark:text-gray-400">
          Content for Bagisto will go here. Use similar Flowbite components like cards, feature lists, etc.
        </p>
      </div>
      </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
    <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl lg:px-6">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-sm text-center mb-8 lg:mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl lg:text-4xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Lunar: Alternatives and Features
        </h2>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-500 sm:text-xl dark:text-gray-400">
          Content for Lunar will go here.
        </p>
      </div>
      </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl lg:px-6">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-sm text-center mb-8 lg:mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl lg:text-4xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Vanilo: Alternatives and Features
        </h2>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-500 sm:text-xl dark:text-gray-400">
          Content for Vanilo will go here.
        </p>
      </div>
      </div>
  </section>

</MainLayout>
